        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You know that you were on the side of tha Allies in the war, and if you cast your memory back, you can remember a small town and a family with too many children.  You can't remember your embrace, or the first few days following it.  Your first memories as a Cainite are coming back to yourself while licking blood from a severed limb.  Eventually an Autarkis Nosferatu found you and explained the details of your new life.  He was clan-loyal more than anything else, and half-convinced the world was ending, but he did right by you.  He was disappointed when you decided to join the Sabbat, but your disjointed memories of family left you wanting more, and if the world was ending, you weren't going to go down easy.    You're deeply loyal to the Sabbat (Praise Caine and pass the cup!), but you are also clan loyal.  You joined your pack to keep an eye on Jessie and potentially kill him.  So far, you haven't seen the need, and you find his goals and work style compatible with yours."
        ],
